HEADWORD: Bonesetter
<hw>Bone"set*ter</hw> <pr>(-s⟦ecr⟧t*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One who sets broken or dislocated bones; -- commonly applied to
one, not a regular surgeon, who makes an occupation of setting
bones.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Bone"set*ting</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boneshaw</ent>⟦br⟧
